-- 
Brazil Court Rejects Lawsuit Against Cigarette Makers

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-05-27T13:43:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/brazil-court-rejects-lawsuit-against-cigarette-makers-1-.html
A Brazilian court rejected a class
action against cigarette makers  Souza Cruz SA (CRUZ3)  and Philip Morris
Inc. for injuries to smokers, Souza Cruz said in a statement.  The Association for the Defense of the Health of Smokers
requested in the lawsuit more than 30 billion reais ($18.7
billion) in compensation, according to the statement distributed
by PR Newswire.  Souza Cruz rose 1.1 percent to 18.65 reais in  Sao Paulo 
trading at 9:39 a.m. New York time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helder Marinho in Sao Paulo at 
 hmarinho@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Telma Marotto at 
 tmarotto1@bloomberg.net  